Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.48,0:00:07.91,Default,,0,0,0,,We have innate within us\Na tremendous intense
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.91,0:00:13.12,Default,,0,0,0,,powerful\Ndevotion.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.12,0:00:20.24,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have to develop it. You only\Nhave to rediscover it.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.24,0:00:26.88,Default,,0,0,0,,There is with within us already\Npre-existent
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.88,0:00:35.12,Default,,0,0,0,,an energy of such enormous power\Nthat one sums up that power
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.12,0:00:44.23,Default,,0,0,0,,to relinquish any and every attachment\Nthat stands in the way.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.23,0:00:50.16,Default,,0,0,0,,You won't find the willingness to do\Nthat within the ego structure.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.16,0:00:58.39,Default,,0,0,0,,The eagle will instantly give you an\Nargument why it should not persist
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.39,0:01:04.87,Default,,0,0,0,,in the direction that it's positioned.\NSo one has to reach deeper within
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.87,0:01:12.88,Default,,0,0,0,,oneself.\NAt the very innate core of one's being
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.88,0:01:20.32,Default,,0,0,0,,is a spiritual power\Nof enormous strength
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.32,0:01:25.75,Default,,0,0,0,,which alone can accomplish the\Nimpossible.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.75,0:01:30.79,Default,,0,0,0,,The ego\Nin and of itself cannot transcend
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.79,0:01:39.75,Default,,0,0,0,,itself.\NIt requires the presence of God.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.75,0:01:46.88,Default,,0,0,0,,It is by divine grace that one\Ntranscends the ego.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.88,0:01:55.36,Default,,0,0,0,,It is by divine grace\None moves from mind to no mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.36,0:02:02.32,Default,,0,0,0,,It's by divine grace one moves from\Nthinking
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.32,0:02:10.08,Default,,0,0,0,,that content and linearity is the\Nultimate reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.08,0:02:16.48,Default,,0,0,0,,It's by divine grace.\NNow, no one would be here to pursue such
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.48,0:02:23.84,Default,,0,0,0,,a goal\Nif such grace did not already pre-exist.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.84,0:02:28.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, each and every one of us here\Nthis day
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.40,0:02:37.28,Default,,0,0,0,,is here by virtue of divine grace.\NTherefore,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.28,0:02:43.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I pray to the divine grace in thee and\Nbless it. acknowledge it
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.76,0:02:50.40,Default,,0,0,0,,because it is the divinity of that grace\Nby which we all exist at this moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.40,0:02:58.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?\NSo that which you're looking for is not
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.80,0:03:02.95,Default,,0,0,0,,beyond you. It's not something you have\Nto develop.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.95,0:03:10.31,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not something you have to search\Nfor.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.31,0:03:23.59,Default,,0,0,0,,One only surreners to that which already\Nexists.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.59,0:03:29.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I want the music now.\NThe purpose of the music is that it
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.59,0:03:34.72,Default,,0,0,0,,takes us out of content and it tends to\Nput us in context. It tends to take us
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.72,0:03:53.20,Default,,0,0,0,,out of the linear,\Nput us in the nonlinear.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.20,0:04:25.12,Default,,0,0,0,,his own.\NHe be
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.12,0:04:39.52,Default,,0,0,0,,The name\Nis
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.52,0:05:00.80,Default,,0,0,0,,here.\Nsong.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.80,0:05:18.16,Default,,0,0,0,,He\Nand
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.16,0:05:23.52,Default,,0,0,0,,song.\NWe
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.52,0:05:43.03,Default,,0,0,0,,are\Nall
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.03,0:06:04.24,Default,,0,0,0,,he\Nis all
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.24,0:06:32.08,Default,,0,0,0,,he\NKeep We are
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.08,0:06:46.40,Default,,0,0,0,,the\Nsong.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.40,0:07:07.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Here we are.\Nsong.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.59,0:07:46.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Give me\NHeaven
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.31,0:08:07.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh,\Nhere we are.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.19,0:08:32.15,Default,,0,0,0,,song.\NSo
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.15,0:08:53.27,Default,,0,0,0,,he\Nsong.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.27,0:09:11.36,Default,,0,0,0,,He\NIt swells up from within oneself.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.36,0:09:19.76,Default,,0,0,0,,The music merely creates the field which\Nallows it to come up. And that power
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.76,0:09:26.80,Default,,0,0,0,,is there at all times.\NBy being together today, we affirm its
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.80,0:09:42.95,Default,,0,0,0,,presence within all of us.\NWell, I didn't die at all after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.95,0:09:49.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Weakness, faintness,\Nand dying was happening on the stage.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.68,0:09:54.24,Default,,0,0,0,,And then I walked down the field and it\Nstopped.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.24,0:10:03.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Could still be. So, what would could be\Nbetter?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.27,0:10:10.72,Default,,0,0,0,,What a wonderful place to\Nexpire.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.72,0:10:16.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Came close.\NLet's see.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.72,0:10:22.39,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what it was. Is this That's what\Nit was.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.39,0:10:31.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay. So, maybe we should take a break\Nthen.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.12,0:10:37.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't know if I'd make it to the back\Nof the room or not.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.04,0:10:41.83,Default,,0,0,0,,And then we'll have questions and\Nanswers. Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.83,0:10:45.20,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Please speak about drugs and levels of\Nconsciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.20,0:10:48.48,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Drugs.\N>> Drugs.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.48,0:10:57.92,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Like penicellin.\N>> Yeah. Like penicellin.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.92,0:11:03.83,Default,,0,0,0,,You see the\Nthe power of addiction is this.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.83,0:11:08.24,Default,,0,0,0,,We need the calibrated levels of\Nconsciousness thing up there. Huh? What
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.24,0:11:14.00,Default,,0,0,0,,the what the drug does is anesthetize\Nyour perception
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.00,0:11:21.83,Default,,0,0,0,,of the lower levels of consciousness.\NYeah. Levels of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.83,0:11:30.24,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Okay.\NAll right. So, a drug cal drugs
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.24,0:11:37.20,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrate around 70 or 80. Alcohol,\Ndrugs. What they do is they
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.20,0:11:41.60,Default,,0,0,0,,anesthetize\Nall this down here
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.60,0:11:47.60,Default,,0,0,0,,and suddenly you go into a state of a\Nsense of well-being, joy, love, love
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.60,0:11:53.36,Default,,0,0,0,,everyone, contentment,\Nserenity.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.36,0:11:59.04,Default,,0,0,0,,The drug doesn't cause this. What it\Ndoes is it blocks these out.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.04,0:12:03.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Now you get to experience what is there\Nall the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.76,0:12:08.88,Default,,0,0,0,,You think, isn't that drug wonderful?\NLook what it's done for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.88,0:12:14.63,Default,,0,0,0,,So the error is to ascribe the power to\Nthe drug and think a co in terms of
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.63,0:12:20.39,Default,,0,0,0,,causality that drug is causing this. No,\Nthis drug does not have the power to
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.39,0:12:26.72,Default,,0,0,0,,cause that.\NDrugs calibrate 80 to 90s. I say, but
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.72,0:12:36.95,Default,,0,0,0,,what the drug does is blot all this out.\NAnd now you feel like I just felt a
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.95,0:12:42.72,Default,,0,0,0,,short while ago.\NSort of exquisite, ecstatic, joyful
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.72,0:12:49.83,Default,,0,0,0,,serenity.\Nconsequently not to do that again. You'd
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.83,0:12:58.32,Default,,0,0,0,,be an idiot, wouldn't you?\NYou'd really have to be stupid if
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.32,0:13:02.72,Default,,0,0,0,,something\Nthat cost you $4 put you in that
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.72,0:13:08.80,Default,,0,0,0,,condition.\NWell,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.80,0:13:16.00,Default,,0,0,0,,the field is so powerful. One exposure\Nis all you need. You will never be the
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.00,0:13:22.63,Default,,0,0,0,,same again. Anybody\Nwho's experienced up here will never be
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.63,0:13:29.20,Default,,0,0,0,,satisfied with anything less.\NAs the Buddha said, once you have heard
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.20,0:13:34.16,Default,,0,0,0,,of enlightenment,\Nyou will never be satisfied with
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.16,0:13:41.68,Default,,0,0,0,,anything less.\NThe person then becomes so powerfully
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.68,0:13:52.07,Default,,0,0,0,,reprogrammed, re\NThe person is never the same again.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.07,0:13:57.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Once you've been in Shangla, the memory\Nof Shangala is seared into your memory.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.36,0:14:04.32,Default,,0,0,0,,By comparison, everything else in this\Nworld is pale.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.32,0:14:11.83,Default,,0,0,0,,The experience of the presence of God\Nis so overwhelming
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.83,0:14:17.04,Default,,0,0,0,,that it is transformative. And people\Nwho have had near-death experiences
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.04,0:14:29.04,Default,,0,0,0,,to once go into that knowingness,\Nall else in the world fades away. Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.04,0:14:37.27,Default,,0,0,0,,That memory is seared in your memory.\NThat's what's possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.27,0:14:48.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Now to return to Shangerla by any means\Neven if it cost you your life.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.07,0:14:55.83,Default,,0,0,0,,So the doctor says you keep doing that\Nand you'll die.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.83,0:15:00.80,Default,,0,0,0,,After being told that, you leave the\Ndoctor's office
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.80,0:15:09.36,Default,,0,0,0,,and you go to the bar and order a double\Nmartini.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.36,0:15:13.19,Default,,0,0,0,,You say to the bartender, "Guess what\Nthe doc told me?" He says, "I keep
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.19,0:15:24.07,Default,,0,0,0,,drinking. I'm dead as a duck."\NYou don't say. The bartender is
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.07,0:15:31.51,Default,,0,0,0,,consequently anything to overcome that\Naddiction has to be of equal power.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.51,0:15:37.36,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, because now we're talking about\Npower. We're talking about logarithmic
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.36,0:15:42.00,Default,,0,0,0,,power.\NThis is not a little higher than this.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.00,0:15:47.12,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a whole different dimension of\Nexperiencing life.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.12,0:15:52.56,Default,,0,0,0,,This is so powerful that it's\Nunforgettable and sears itself in one's
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.56,0:15:59.83,Default,,0,0,0,,memory.\NSo the desire to reexperience that high
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.83,0:16:05.92,Default,,0,0,0,,is actually the desire\Nto return to God.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.92,0:16:13.12,Default,,0,0,0,,The person doesn't know that\Nthe exquisite bliss of the presence of
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.12,0:16:20.63,Default,,0,0,0,,God is overwhelming.\Nwipes out everything. Life, children,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.63,0:16:27.04,Default,,0,0,0,,wives, physical life, physical death\Nitself.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.04,0:16:33.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Any program to overcome it then has to\Nbe promised an equal dimension.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.19,0:16:40.80,Default,,0,0,0,,So the recovery programs from drugs have\Nto calibrate over 540.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.80,0:16:44.95,Default,,0,0,0,,And as a matter of fact, they do\Ncalibrate at 540.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.95,0:16:49.19,Default,,0,0,0,,It takes the power of unconditional love\Nwhich is a quality of the presence of
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.19,0:17:00.32,Default,,0,0,0,,God to overcome that powerful addiction.\NTherefore,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.32,0:17:06.31,Default,,0,0,0,,the addict is a victim of an illusion\Nthat it comes from out there. What he
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.31,0:17:12.95,Default,,0,0,0,,doesn't know is that what he experiences\Nis the liberation of the experience of
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.95,0:17:20.40,Default,,0,0,0,,his own inner self.\NSo
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.40,0:17:25.43,Default,,0,0,0,,>> what is self sabotage? What what causes\Nself?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.43,0:17:30.32,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Well, it we depend what one means.\NConscious or unconscious.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.32,0:17:34.79,Default,,0,0,0,,The appeal of destroying oneself is like\Nan addiction.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.79,0:17:41.12,Default,,0,0,0,,You get hooked on degradation, poverty,\Nsacrifice, suffering, filth,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.12,0:17:45.67,Default,,0,0,0,,being the victim.\NAnd the juice you get out of all that is
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.67,0:17:53.91,Default,,0,0,0,,tremendous.\NThe juice of being the victim can't be
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.91,0:17:58.40,Default,,0,0,0,,beat in this world.\NI mean, other than being enlightened,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.40,0:18:02.79,Default,,0,0,0,,the juice of being victim is hard to\Nbeat.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.79,0:18:13.20,Default,,0,0,0,,You have the trial lawyers on your side.\NYou can beat up McDonald's.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.20,0:18:16.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody is thronging to be the victim.\NThere's great competition for
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.88,0:18:26.72,Default,,0,0,0,,victimhood, you know.\NSo the trial lawyers association and the
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.72,0:18:33.20,Default,,0,0,0,,judic judiciary backs up that whole idea\Nof no responsibility. The cause is out
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.20,0:18:37.12,Default,,0,0,0,,there. The cause is always deep pockets.\NSomehow the cause always has deep
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.12,0:18:40.72,Default,,0,0,0,,pockets.\NYou never hear of a poor woman being
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.72,0:18:46.24,Default,,0,0,0,,sued because somebody fell on the snow\Nin her on her in front of her sidewalk.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.24,0:18:51.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Gimbals, yes. Poor lady on the corner,\Nno. It only happens if you have deep
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.67,0:18:57.28,Default,,0,0,0,,pockets. Oh, yes. The remuneration.\NThere's a peculiar thing about the
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.28,0:19:01.28,Default,,0,0,0,,unconscious.\NYou know, I was in practice over 50
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.28,0:19:06.55,Default,,0,0,0,,years, 52 years, 55 years, whatever.\NAnd I've treated many people on
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.55,0:19:12.08,Default,,0,0,0,,disability.\NI remember one guy was run over by a
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.08,0:19:16.32,Default,,0,0,0,,backhole.\NI mean, this guy was crushed. You know
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.32,0:19:22.24,Default,,0,0,0,,what I'm saying?\NI mean, to be run over by a backhole
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.24,0:19:28.72,Default,,0,0,0,,did bust him up.\NAnd so he was on workman's comp. Well,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.72,0:19:33.60,Default,,0,0,0,,he had a a workman's comp is very\Nniggerly
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.60,0:19:38.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and you have to really threaten them,\Nbeat them up, and get a lawyer. You
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.96,0:19:42.24,Default,,0,0,0,,know, if I was running workman's comp,\NI'd say, "How about 20 grand? Will I
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.24,0:19:46.96,Default,,0,0,0,,make you happy?" Yeah. No. They they\Nwon't give them the 20 grand. So 15
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.96,0:19:51.44,Default,,0,0,0,,years later at the cost of $250,000 in\Nlegal fees on the part of Workman's
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.44,0:19:56.88,Default,,0,0,0,,comp, they now come across. Well,\Nanyway, this guy is fighting Workman's
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.88,0:20:00.96,Default,,0,0,0,,comp\Nand he's disabled. This was a very
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.96,0:20:06.88,Default,,0,0,0,,honest man.\NHe had pain. He had uh disability. He
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.88,0:20:12.16,Default,,0,0,0,,was unemployable.\NAnd finally workman's comp case got
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.16,0:20:16.96,Default,,0,0,0,,solved.\NHe got 50,000 or whatever it was. Do you
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.96,0:20:22.40,Default,,0,0,0,,know within a week he had a job?\NWithin a week he was a a guard in a
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.40,0:20:25.67,Default,,0,0,0,,bank.\NNow this was not conscious. It's
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.67,0:20:29.76,Default,,0,0,0,,different than malingering. Malingering\Nis a conscious choice. No, this is in
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.76,0:20:34.48,Default,,0,0,0,,the unconscious.\NOnce you're on disability, forget it
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.48,0:20:38.32,Default,,0,0,0,,because it sets up an unconscious\Nmechanism
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.32,0:20:44.72,Default,,0,0,0,,which keeps you disabled. You don't\Nchoose to have arthritis, fibromyalgia,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.72,0:20:52.40,Default,,0,0,0,,asthma, coughs, diarrhea, headaches, and\Ngoing blind with buzzing in your ears.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.40,0:20:57.28,Default,,0,0,0,,But when the disability settles up,\Nsomehow they disappear.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.28,0:21:03.84,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just not within conscious control.\NIt's not, you know, so there are things
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.84,0:21:08.40,Default,,0,0,0,,operating in the psyche over which we\Ndon't have conscious control. That's why
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.40,0:21:13.12,Default,,0,0,0,,everybody deserves our compassion\Nbecause as hard as you try to be
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.12,0:21:17.52,Default,,0,0,0,,conscious of it and I'm sure this\Ngentleman who I treated was a very
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.52,0:21:22.64,Default,,0,0,0,,honorable man. He was a blue collar blue\Ncollar guy. I mean a straight blue
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.64,0:21:27.91,Default,,0,0,0,,collar guy you know and deception would\Njust an advent to him. He would never
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.91,0:21:33.44,Default,,0,0,0,,have thought of of using deception at\Nall. And yet that mechanism was so
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.44,0:21:38.88,Default,,0,0,0,,powerful because I can remember you know\Nwithin a week or two he was working as
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.88,0:21:43.60,Default,,0,0,0,,he said I don't know I just feel\Nstronger or something but his commitment
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.60,0:21:51.28,Default,,0,0,0,,to life returned and uh\Nand he worked as a uh guard in a uh in a
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.28,0:21:56.24,Default,,0,0,0,,bank. Yes. Yeah.\N>> And he to this day he's okay again.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.24,0:22:00.79,Default,,0,0,0,,>> But you know it's like when it gets hold\Nof you you can't let you can't get away
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.79,0:22:04.55,Default,,0,0,0,,from it. So yes,\N>> what is the source of early morning
